Somebody recently asked for an indentation mode for Objective Caml.

I made one. It works with the full syntax of both O'Caml and O'Labl,
and provides an indentation almost identical to the one you can see in 
O'Caml sources.

It also includes regexps for hilit19 and font-lock.

You can find it at

	http://wwwfun.kurims.kyoto-u.ac.jp/soft/olabl/
	ftp://ftp.kurims.kyoto-u.ac.jp/pub/lang/olabl/ocaml-mode-1.02.tar.gz

